# Mitigation

Holding strong on Win10 but we are vulerable. If you don't have exteded support you will be vulnerable to RedSun basically forever.

One mitigation I figured out might atleast stop NORMAL user to escalate to SYSTEM is the following:

Block the Payload Execution (AppLocker / WDAC):

Open RegEdit and navigate to HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\CLSID\{50d185b9-fff3-4656-92c7-e4018da4361d}

BEFORE ANYTHING ELSE, EXPORT THAT REGISTRY ENTRY!

You can use script "RedSun_Mitigate.bat" to open the key and make a backup (It will appear on Desktop).

When regedit opens and backup is made, right click on the key {50d185b9-fff3-4656-92c7-e4018da4361d} -> Permissions -> Advanced. You will see owner is TrustedInstaller, we will change it to Administrator. 

Click Change and type in the box ADMINISTRATORS and then hit Check Names. Check the box that says "Replace owner on subcontainers and objects", then hit Apply.

That is it. I still recommend 0patch but atleast you have some protection against this nasty exploit because now attacker needs to be admin or else exploit will return ACCESS_DENIED.

Keep strong Win 10 brothers and sisters!
